    "value": "Pleiades Neo consists of two identical satellites delivering native 30cm resolution optical and multispectral imagery with location accuracy of 3.5m CE90. The constellation is entirely funded, manufactured, owned and operated by Airbus. Since its launch in 2021, the company says the constellation has changed Earth observation based services. A successor, Pleiades Neo Next, is planned with native resolution in the 20cm class.",
